29/03/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Groups of anarchist youths clashed with police during street riots in Athens and the second largest city, Thessaloniki, early on Saturday (March 28th). 
Hooded youths attacked department stores in Thessaloniki to protest against the arrest of two of their associates. 
The group also set fire to a bank. 
One police officer suffered injuries in Athens, media reported. 
(ANA-MPA, In.news, SKAI, AFP, FoNet - 28/03/09)
